        "text": "I am concerned about the growing trend of video game companies shutting down access to games that consumers have paid for. The Digital Fairness Act is an opportunity to safeguard ownership rights, and I ask the European Commission to take into account the Stop Killing Games initiative. At its core, the principle should be simple: if you buy it, you own it. Digital purchases must carry the same expectation of lasting access and value as physical goods.",
